In a large mixing bowl, beat butter and sugar until crumbly. Beat in the lemon juice, egg yolk, flour, lemon peel and salt; mix well. Gradually beat in milk. In another large mixing bowl, beat egg whites until stiff peaks form; gently fold into lemon mixture. Pour into an ungreased 1-qt. baking dish. Place the dish in a 13-in. x 9-in. x 2-in. baking dish. Pour boiling water into the larger baking dish to a depth of 1 in. Bake at 325 degrees F for 40-45 minutes or until a knife inserted near the center comes out clean and top is golden. Serve warm.